mirage1@gpu.utcs.utoronto.ca (Robert Ames) writes:
: I want to make up a business card with an RSA public key on it.  Has
: anyone done this?  Does one simply use the 'e' and 'n' key components in
: base-64 PEM format, or is there more to it?
 
Perhaps an RFC1113-encoded version of the Distinguished Encoding
Rules encoding of the key would be the way to go.  That's what I
chose for the PEM program I'm working on
See the "pkcs" documents on rsa.com.

Let's hope that people who receive your business card have access
to an OCR device.  There's got to be a better way to disseminate keys...

Mark Riordan
